        overview_lead: "This section starts with three things: what changed today in the official docs, which model/surface choices are current, and where first-time and professional users should begin.",
        overview_update_1_title: "Model and surface matrix rechecked",
        overview_update_1_desc: "The run started by re-checking `codex/models`, confirming that `gpt-5.5` is still the top recommendation, that `gpt-5.4` remains the fallback path, and clarifying how `gpt-5.4-mini` and `gpt-5.3-codex` split roles. I also made the login-path distinction explicit up front: inside Codex, `gpt-5.5` currently appears only with ChatGPT sign-in, not API-key authentication.",
        overview_update_2_title: "Pricing and credits refreshed",
        overview_update_2_desc: "The guide now reflects the `GPT-5.5` usage tables, `Free $0`, `Go $8`, `Plus $20`, `Pro from $100`, the Business/Enterprise Codex-only pay-as-you-go path, and the current Plus / Pro 5x / Pro 20x / Business / API Key pricing layout. It also keeps the current split where token-based credit tables apply first to Business and new Enterprise while other plans still reference message-based ranges, and it now calls out that the current Pro promos run through May 31, 2026.",
