        overview_update_3_desc: "The top path still keeps App-first onboarding separate from IDE/CLI + Docs MCP professional workflows in Quickstart, but now also spells out API-key sign-in limits and the Windows/WSL path more clearly.",
        overview_update_4_title: "April app updates folded in",
        overview_update_4_desc: "I cross-checked the April 16, 2026 `Codex for (almost) everything` launch post against `app/features` and `app/automations`, then folded background computer use, more plugins, multiple terminal tabs, SSH devboxes, and richer artifact/sidebar flows back into the guide structure.",
        overview_update_5_title: "Broader launch-post sweep",
        overview_update_5_desc: "I re-read `developers.openai.com/codex`, `openai.com/index`, and `openai.com/codex` together to compare the April 23 `Introducing GPT-5.5` launch, the April 16 `Codex for (almost) everything` update, the April 2 `Codex now offers pay-as-you-go pricing for teams` launch, the March 17 `GPT-5.4 mini and nano` launch, the February 12 `GPT-5.3-Codex-Spark` launch, and the latest app/plugins/skills/automations docs. This run updates the top toggle and the model/app/pricing explanations directly instead of adding a new chapter.",
